[2] USA (Wisconsin)
Date: Wed 21 Feb 2018
Source: Florence Forest News [edited]
https://www.florence-forestnews.com/2018/02/21/florence-county-pertussis-count-continues-to-rise/


Pertussis has increased to 17 laboratory-confirmed cases for 2018 in Florence County. The Health Department, following CDC guidelines, continues to contact each case to assure household contacts are treated and anyone symptomatic (coughing) is tested. Confirmed cases are isolated for 5 days while taking antibiotic treatment and may not participate in school or work.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Florence County, with a population of 4423 residents in 2010, is located in the northeastern part of U.S. state of Wisconsin, bordering on the north the Upper Peninsula of the U.S. state of Michigan (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florence_County,_Wisconsin#Geography).

