[3] Nigeria (Adamawa)
Date: Sun 21 Jan 2018
Source: Reliefweb [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/adamawa-state-integrated-disease-surveillance-and-response-idsr-nigeria-emergency-0


Outbreak investigation of 71 cases of suspected cases of pertussis (whooping cough) were reported from Kasuwan Gada (41 cases) in Lokuwa ward and Blue house (30 cases) in Vintim wards of Mubi North LGA of Adamawa State - The LGA health department was able to mobilize amoxicillin and paracetamol to support case management but no erythromycin or azithromycin. The communities were sensitized on the need for completion of routine immunization, prompt treatment of cases of pertussis and how to reduce the transmission within communities.

