[East Java is a province of Indonesia located in eastern Java; it includes the island of Madura, which is connected to Java by the longest bridge in Indonesia, the Suramadu Bridge, as well as the Kangean and Masalembu archipelagos located further east and north, respectively (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Java). Its capital is Surabaya, the 2nd largest city in Indonesia and a major industrial center. A map of java showing the location of East Java can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/East+Java,+Indonesia. - Mod.ML]

